  "time_ut": 1658377938,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dd0\u0daf \u0db4\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0daf\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0da7 \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dd9\u0dc0\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dcf\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dc5 \u0d9a\u0dc3\u0dbd \u0dad\u0dda \u0dad\u0ddc\u0d9c\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Catches a shipment of junk tea ready for sale in the Middle East",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Officials of the Special Task Force said that a person was arrested from a Modara Ellihouse Road warehouse with a stock of waste tea prepared to be sold in the international market under the name of Ceylon Tea.",
        "19,072.86 kilos of waste tea and 336 liters of liquid used for coloring waste tea have also been taken into police custody.",
        "It is also reported that this waste tea was prepared to be exported to the Middle East countries and it is also reported that due to this waste tea being released to the international market under the name of Ceylon Tea, the sale of tea in Sri Lanka is experiencing a big setback internationally.",
        "Under the supervision of Senior Superintendent of Police J.R. Senadheera, who is in charge of Western North, as per the instructions of Special Task Force Commanding Officer Mr. Varuna Jayasundara, Inspector HPMSK of the Special Task Force Gonahena camp. The raid was carried out by a team of officers including Veerakkodi."
      ],
